Here's my offer: "The Book Mountain" in Speichenis, so-called Bookenberg!
Nine years later, this mountain, worth 30 million euros, grew.
It is part of the revitalisation project, which also includes an underground garage, a supermarket, a post office and several surrounding houses and a total of 50 apartments.
At the beginning of November, the "Bloody Mountain" was the second prize of the 2012 Best Library of the Netherlands.
The project also participates in the 2012 Dutch national woodwork competition.
Thus, a faceless suburb that had never been able to offer anything but a postmodern pedestrian zone and a surprisingly ugly town town whose white facades suggest a milk plant has become richer on one modern piece of architecture.
But most importantly, there's the first cultural public building in the history of this town.
Long Road to Book
First impression: book Eldorado under a cheese cap.
There's only one elevator in the middle of the mountain, because true architects and readers would prefer to explore this area on foot.
