This city has been overstretched in the best time possible, and steel fences have been erected since Monday, cutting several key highways to the capital and causing chaos on the roads.
However, this was not to prevent people from getting to work from the suburbs, but to prevent protesters from getting to the Parliament.
On Sunday, the new head of Mexico, Henrique Peña Nieto, will put on a Presidential link and take over the country.
He's got a difficult task ahead of him.
